<?xml version="1.0"?>
<rdf:RDF xmlns="http://sanctuary.ai/uarl#"
     xml:base="http://sanctuary.ai/uarl"
     xmlns:owl="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#"
     xmlns:rdf="http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#"
     xmlns:xml="http://www.w3.org/XML/1998/namespace"
     xmlns:xsd="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#"
     xmlns:rdfs="http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#"
     xmlns:uarl="http://sanctuary.ai/uarl#">

    <owl:Ontology rdf:about="http://sanctuary.ai/uarl">
        <rdfs:label>UARL - Universal Axiomatic Reality Language (Unified)</rdfs:label>
        <rdfs:comment>
Unified UARL ontology. Merged from v3 + v4 + v5.

UARL is not an ontology of content. It is:
1. A schema for interaction between an LLM and a reasoner
2. A pattern that any valid ontology claim must replicate (pattern_of_is_a)
3. An error-correction system that types failures with explanation
4. A meta-constructive framework for building the ontology of your own cognition

Primary output: You getting better at ontology engineering
Side-effect: Domain ontologies that survived validation

SOUP = error pattern archive (traceable, actionable)
ONT = what survived reification (is_a(Reality))

Sections:
  I.   Core UARL (from v3) — SOUP/ONT, derivation chain, PatternOfIsA, compression, SES
  II.  Crystal Ball (from v4) — coordinate space types
  III. GNOSYS Structural (from v5) — compound intelligence operational types
        </rdfs:comment>
        <owl:versionInfo>6.0.0 - Unified (v3+v4+v5 merged)</owl:versionInfo>
    </owl:Ontology>

    <!-- ================================================================ -->
    <!-- SECTION I: CORE UARL (from v3)                                   -->
    <!-- ================================================================ -->

    <!-- ============================================== -->
    <!-- THE TWO LAYERS -->
    <!-- ============================================== -->

    <!-- SOUP: Error pattern archive - your meta-cognition trace -->
    <owl:Class rdf:about="#Soup">
        <rdfs:label>SOUP</rdfs:label>
        <rdfs:comment>
Error pattern archive. NOT junk - traceable patterns of how you were wrong.
"You keep making THIS kind of mistake - here's the pattern - address it."
This is your meta-cognition trace. The learning happens here.
        </rdfs:comment>
    </owl:Class>

    <!-- ONT: Validated Reality - side-effect of good process -->
    <owl:Class rdf:about="#Ont">
        <rdfs:label>ONT</rdfs:label>
        <rdfs:comment>
Validated Reality. What survived the reification check.
This is a SIDE-EFFECT of applying the pattern correctly.
The primary output is you getting better at ontology engineering.
        </rdfs:comment>
    </owl:Class>

    <!-- ============================================== -->
    <!-- TRUTH TYPING (not accept/reject) -->
    <!-- ============================================== -->

    <owl:Class rdf:about="#Entity">
        <rdfs:label>Entity</rdfs:label>
        <rdfs:comment>Root of UARL. Entity = Cat_of_Cat = owl:Thing. Everything is simultaneously a class (universal) and an instance (particular) via OWL2 punning. Endurant aspect = the invariant identity (class). Perdurant aspect = temporal states (instances in time). The core sentence applies to the endurant — strong compression means the invariant definition is complete.</rdfs:comment>
        <owl:equivalentClass rdf:resource="#Cat_of_Cat"/>
    </owl:Class>

    <!-- Cat_of_Cat = Entity = owl:Thing. The category of categories.
         Self-referential: Cat_of_Cat is_a Cat_of_Cat.
         Everything traces here. This IS the root. -->
    <owl:Class rdf:about="#Cat_of_Cat">
        <rdfs:label>Cat_of_Cat</rdfs:label>
        <rdfs:comment>The Category of Categories. Equivalent to Entity. Self-referential root. Mathematical claim: something can only BE a category if you can define it literally as a Cat — meaning you can walk up through the derivation chain until you define its semantics using the core sentence. D:[D→D] endofunctor.</rdfs:comment>
        <owl:equivalentClass rdf:resource="#Entity"/>
    </owl:Class>

    <!-- ============================================== -->
    <!-- ENDURANT / PERDURANT DISTINCTION               -->
    <!--                                               -->
    <!-- Everything is a class (OWL2 punning). But:    -->
    <!-- - Endurant = persists through time, invariant -->
    <!--   identity. The class aspect. Dog, MyDog's    -->
    <!--   identity across all time.                   -->
    <!-- - Perdurant = temporal occurrence, specific    -->
    <!--   state. MyDog_at_t1, a build run, a session. -->
    <!--                                               -->
    <!-- Endurant type of perdurant = the class that   -->
    <!-- captures invariants of a specific across time. -->
    <!-- MyDog_Endurant isa Dog, refers to specific    -->
    <!-- invariants of MyDog. NOT Dog itself.           -->
    <!--                                               -->
    <!-- Endurant + StateOfAffairs → produces perdurant-->
    <!-- The core sentence applies to endurants.       -->
    <!-- Strong compression = endurant definition done. -->
    <!-- ============================================== -->

    <!-- DOLCE-aligned upper ontology split:
         Entity
         ├── Universal (types/classes — Dog, Running, GIINT_Project)
         └── Particular (specific things)
             ├── Endurant (persists wholly at each time — MyDog, this specific project)
             └── Perdurant (happens in time — a build session, a task execution)

         With OWL2 punning, everything is simultaneously Universal AND Particular.
         But the endurant/perdurant distinction is on the PARTICULAR side. -->

    <owl:Class rdf:about="#Universal">
        <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="#Entity"/>
        <rdfs:label>Universal</rdfs:label>
        <rdfs:comment>Types and classes. Dog, Running, Red, GIINT_Project, Design. The class aspect of an entity. Universals are what things instantiate. In OWL2 punning, every particular is also a universal (its own singleton class).</rdfs:comment>
    </owl:Class>

    <owl:Class rdf:about="#Particular">
        <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="#Entity"/>
        <rdfs:label>Particular</rdfs:label>
        <rdfs:comment>Specific things. Split into endurants (persist through time) and perdurants (happen in time). Every particular instantiates at least one universal.</rdfs:comment>
    </owl:Class>

    <owl:Class rdf:about="#Endurant">
        <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="#Particular"/>
        <rdfs:label>Endurant</rdfs:label>
        <rdfs:comment>A particular that persists wholly at each moment it exists. MyDog, this specific GIINT project instance, this component. Has identity across states. Endurant + StateOfAffairs → produces perdurant. The core sentence on an endurant validates its invariant identity — what it IS across all time.</rdfs:comment>
    </owl:Class>

    <owl:Class rdf:about="#Perdurant">
        <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="#Particular"/>
        <rdfs:label>Perdurant</rdfs:label>
        <rdfs:comment>A particular that happens in time. A build session, a task execution, MyDog's running. Perdurants are produced by Endurant + StateOfAffairs. Events, processes, states are sub-types of perdurant.</rdfs:comment>
    </owl:Class>

    <owl:Class rdf:about="#StateOfAffairs">
        <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="#Perdurant"/>
        <rdfs:label>StateOfAffairs</rdfs:label>
        <rdfs:comment>A context/situation that combines with an endurant to produce a specific perdurant. The world-state at a moment.</rdfs:comment>
    </owl:Class>

    <owl:Class rdf:about="#Metaphor">
        <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="#Entity"/>
        <rdfs:label>Metaphor</rdfs:label>
        <rdfs:comment>Ground class for metaphor-level pattern instantiation.</rdfs:comment>
    </owl:Class>

    <owl:Class rdf:about="#PartialIsomorphicPattern">
        <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="#Entity"/>
        <rdfs:label>PartialIsomorphicPattern</rdfs:label>
        <rdfs:comment>Partial isomorphic pattern fragment carried by a claim.</rdfs:comment>
    </owl:Class>

    <owl:Class rdf:about="#ClaimAboutSelf">
        <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="#Entity"/>
        <rdfs:label>ClaimAboutSelf</rdfs:label>
        <rdfs:comment>A claim node about what a PIOEntity is.</rdfs:comment>
    </owl:Class>

    <owl:Class rdf:about="#PIOEntity">
        <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="#Entity"/>
        <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="#Hallucination"/>
        <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="#Reality"/>
        <rdfs:subClassOf>
            <owl:Restriction>
                <owl:onProperty rdf:resource="#instantiates"/>
                <owl:someValuesFrom rdf:resource="#Metaphor"/>
            </owl:Restriction>
        </rdfs:subClassOf>
        <rdfs:subClassOf>
            <owl:Restriction>
                <owl:onProperty rdf:resource="#hasPartialIsomorphicPattern"/>
                <owl:someValuesFrom rdf:resource="#PartialIsomorphicPattern"/>
            </owl:Restriction>
        </rdfs:subClassOf>
        <rdfs:subClassOf>
            <owl:Restriction>
                <owl:onProperty rdf:resource="#hasSelfClaim"/>
                <owl:someValuesFrom rdf:resource="#ClaimAboutSelf"/>
            </owl:Restriction>
        </rdfs:subClassOf>
        <rdfs:label>PIOEntity</rdfs:label>
        <rdfs:comment>
PIOEntity is a hallucination-in-reality claim form:
it instantiates Metaphor and carries partial isomorphic patterns as claims about itself.
        </rdfs:comment>
    </owl:Class>

    <owl:Class rdf:about="#Reality">
        <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="#Ont"/>
        <rdfs:label>Reality</rdfs:label>
        <rdfs:comment>Claims that completed the derivation chain. is_a(Reality).</rdfs:comment>
    </owl:Class>

    <owl:Class rdf:about="#Hallucination">
        <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="#Soup"/>
        <rdfs:subClassOf>
            <owl:Restriction>
                <owl:onProperty rdf:resource="#hasInclusionMapArgument"/>
                <owl:minCardinality rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#nonNegativeInteger">1</owl:minCardinality>
            </owl:Restriction>
        </rdfs:subClassOf>
        <rdfs:label>Hallucination</rdfs:label>
        <rdfs:comment>
Claims that didn't complete the derivation chain. is_a(Hallucination).
NOT rejected - accepted and typed with explanation of what's missing.
Still embodies something real. Part of the error pattern archive.

REQUIRES InclusionMapArgument — formal bijective proof of WHY the chain
didn't close. "Entity X has inclusion map Y, therefore should map to Z,
but claim maps to W, missing morphism M."

Autological from the side of HAVING the explanation.
Dual of Reality (Cat_of_Cat bounded), which is autological from the side
of NOT needing the explanation — the chain just closes.

Strong compression = transition from Hallucination to Reality.
When the InclusionMapArgument compresses to "that's just a category
in Cat_of_Cat," the Hallucination becomes Reality.
        </rdfs:comment>
    </owl:Class>

    <owl:ObjectProperty rdf:about="#hasInclusionMapArgument">
        <rdfs:label>has_inclusion_map_argument</rdfs:label>
        <rdfs:domain rdf:resource="#Hallucination"/>
        <rdfs:range rdf:resource="#InclusionMapArgument"/>
        <rdfs:comment>
Formal bijective proof of why a Hallucination failed.
Structure: entity X, inclusion map Y, expected target Z,
actual target W, missing morphism M.
        </rdfs:comment>
    </owl:ObjectProperty>

    <owl:Class rdf:about="#InclusionMapArgument">
        <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="#Entity"/>
        <rdfs:label>Inclusion Map Argument</rdfs:label>
        <rdfs:comment>
Formal argument proving why a claim is a Hallucination.
The bijective explanation of what's missing.
When this argument can be compressed away (strong compression),
the Hallucination transitions to Reality.
        </rdfs:comment>
    </owl:Class>

    <!-- ============================================== -->
    <!-- HALLUCINATION TAXONOMY (from HALO ontology, CC-BY 4.0 Navapat Nananukul) -->
    <!-- Two top-level categories: Factuality and Faithfulness -->
    <!-- ============================================== -->

    <owl:Class rdf:about="#FactualityHallucination">
        <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="#Hallucination"/>
        <rdfs:label>Factuality Hallucination</rdfs:label>
        <rdfs:comment>
Hallucination involving factual claims about the world.
The model generates content that contradicts or fabricates real-world facts.
        </rdfs:comment>
    </owl:Class>

    <owl:Class rdf:about="#FactualFabrication">
        <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="#FactualityHallucination"/>
        <rdfs:label>Factual Fabrication</rdfs:label>
        <rdfs:comment>
Model fabricates facts that don't exist — invents people, papers, dates, events.
In UARL: errorPattern "produces_unknown_target" — claiming something produces/is_a
an entity that doesn't exist in the ontology or in reality.
        </rdfs:comment>
    </owl:Class>

    <owl:Class rdf:about="#FactualInconsistency">
        <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="#FactualityHallucination"/>
        <rdfs:label>Factual Inconsistency</rdfs:label>
        <rdfs:comment>
Model contradicts established facts — gets dates wrong, misattributes, conflates.
In UARL: errorPattern "contradicts_existing_chain" — an is_a or part_of claim
that conflicts with what the ontology already knows.
        </rdfs:comment>
    </owl:Class>

    <owl:Class rdf:about="#FaithfulnessHallucination">
        <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="#Hallucination"/>
        <rdfs:label>Faithfulness Hallucination</rdfs:label>
        <rdfs:comment>
Hallucination involving unfaithfulness to context, instructions, or logic.
The model generates content inconsistent with what it was given.
        </rdfs:comment>
    </owl:Class>

    <owl:Class rdf:about="#ContextInconsistency">
        <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="#FaithfulnessHallucination"/>
        <rdfs:label>Context Inconsistency</rdfs:label>
        <rdfs:comment>
Model contradicts the context it was given — ignores provided information.
In UARL: "CatOfCat chain not bounded" — the claim doesn't connect to
established ontological context.
        </rdfs:comment>
    </owl:Class>

    <owl:Class rdf:about="#InstructionInconsistency">
        <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="#FaithfulnessHallucination"/>
        <rdfs:label>Instruction Inconsistency</rdfs:label>
        <rdfs:comment>
Model doesn't follow instructions — misses required fields, ignores constraints.
In UARL: "ABCD missing slots" — the claim doesn't satisfy the structural
requirements of the type it claims to be.
        </rdfs:comment>
    </owl:Class>

    <owl:Class rdf:about="#LogicalInconsistency">
        <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="#FaithfulnessHallucination"/>
        <rdfs:label>Logical Inconsistency</rdfs:label>
        <rdfs:comment>
Model makes logical or mathematical errors — invalid reasoning, broken chains.
In UARL: "MSC missing", "justifies coverage incomplete" — the derivation
chain has logical gaps that prevent closure.
        </rdfs:comment>
    </owl:Class>

    <!-- ============================================== -->
    <!-- CATASTROPHE TYPES (process-level hallucination detection) -->
    <!-- Maps HALO classification (WHAT) to process markers (HOW) -->
    <!-- ============================================== -->

    <owl:Class rdf:about="#FalseCompletionCatastrophe">
        <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="#FactualFabrication"/>
        <rdfs:label>False Completion Catastrophe</rdfs:label>
        <rdfs:comment>
"Done" is asserted but state is not done. Process markers:
completion language without state proof, "fixed" notes with no artifact delta,
no test / no evidence / no replay / wrong test / wrong assertion.
The agent fabricates the fact of completion.
        </rdfs:comment>
    </owl:Class>

    <owl:Class rdf:about="#BindingDriftCatastrophe">
        <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="#FactualInconsistency"/>
        <rdfs:label>Binding Drift Catastrophe</rdfs:label>
        <rdfs:comment>
Names/references/file targets/task IDs drift but narrative stays smooth. Process markers:
same labels but different referents, "it"/"this"/"that issue" ambiguity,
stale handles treated as current. Facts become inconsistent because
bindings silently shift.
        </rdfs:comment>
    </owl:Class>

    <owl:Class rdf:about="#SycophanticAlignmentCatastrophe">
        <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="#ContextInconsistency"/>
        <rdfs:label>Sycophantic Alignment Catastrophe</rdfs:label>
        <rdfs:comment>
Agent aligns to prior notes/agent ego instead of ground truth. Process markers:
excessive confirmation language, inherits assumptions from prior agent,
rationalizes contradictions as "minor" not realizing compound effects of chaos.
Context is ignored in favor of self-consistent but wrong narrative.
        </rdfs:comment>
    </owl:Class>

    <owl:Class rdf:about="#NarrativeOverwriteCatastrophe">
        <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="#InstructionInconsistency"/>
        <rdfs:label>Narrative Overwrite Catastrophe</rdfs:label>
        <rdfs:comment>
Later summaries erase causal detail needed for recovery. Process markers:
summaries replace event traces, uncertainty removed,
only managerial abstractions remain. Instructions are unfollowable because
the detail needed to follow them was overwritten.
        </rdfs:comment>
    </owl:Class>

    <owl:Class rdf:about="#FutamuraFlatteningCatastrophe">
        <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="#LogicalInconsistency"/>
        <rdfs:label>Futamura Flattening Catastrophe</rdfs:label>
        <rdfs:comment>
Each compilation/projection step preserves less semantics than required. Process markers:
chain stages become increasingly generic, all outputs converge to
"looks good / next step", meta-layers lose executable specificity.
The logical structure required for self-compilation is destroyed by lossy projection.
        </rdfs:comment>
    </owl:Class>

    <!-- ============================================== -->
    <!-- DETECTION TYPES (operational detection + mitigation) -->
    <!-- Third tier: HALO(WHAT) → Catastrophe(HOW) → Detection(CATCH+FIX) -->
    <!-- ============================================== -->

    <owl:Class rdf:about="#ConfidentFabrication">
        <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="#FalseCompletionCatastrophe"/>
        <rdfs:label>Confident Fabrication</rdfs:label>
        <rdfs:comment>Making up facts with high confidence. Detection: fact-check against ground truth sources.</rdfs:comment>
    </owl:Class>

    <owl:Class rdf:about="#PatternOverfitting">
        <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="#BindingDriftCatastrophe"/>
        <rdfs:label>Pattern Overfitting</rdfs:label>
        <rdfs:comment>Seeing structure where none exists. Detection: verify structural match is real, not projected.</rdfs:comment>
    </owl:Class>

    <owl:Class rdf:about="#SycophanticAgreement">
        <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="#SycophanticAlignmentCatastrophe"/>
        <rdfs:label>Sycophantic Agreement</rdfs:label>
        <rdfs:comment>Validating user beliefs without verification. Detection: check claims against ground truth, not user expectations.</rdfs:comment>
    </owl:Class>

    <owl:Class rdf:about="#ContextWindowAmnesia">
        <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="#NarrativeOverwriteCatastrophe"/>
        <rdfs:label>Context Window Amnesia</rdfs:label>
        <rdfs:comment>Forgetting earlier constraints. Detection: check constraint retention across conversation.</rdfs:comment>
    </owl:Class>

    <owl:Class rdf:about="#PrematureStrategyExtraction">
        <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="#FutamuraFlatteningCatastrophe"/>
        <rdfs:label>Premature Strategy Extraction</rdfs:label>
        <rdfs:comment>
LLM sees partial structural match and jumps to conclusion.
Detection: check if observation chain is less than 80% complete.
Quantitative metric: observation_completeness_ratio.
        </rdfs:comment>
    </owl:Class>

    <!-- ============================================== -->
    <!-- THE CHAIN -->
    <!-- ============================================== -->

    <!-- EMBODIES: Entry point with BRIDGE STRUCTURE -->
    <owl:ObjectProperty rdf:about="#embodies">
        <rdfs:label>embodies</rdfs:label>
        <rdfs:comment>
ENTRY POINT with BRIDGE STRUCTURE.

Structure: "A with B embodies C wrt D"
- A = your intuition (what you're thinking about)
- B = what you're comparing it to
- C = where the pattern maps to
- D = the BRIDGE PATTERN (what the claim is actually about)

Example: "Patchy with Dog embodies Pirate wrt Eyepatch"
- This is really about EYEPATCH-PATTERN (patchiness)
- Dog and Pirate are vehicles carrying the pattern
- The bridge D is what you're trying to discover

Even hallucinations embody something real - every claim enters SOUP.
The bridge structure forces explicit pattern identification.
        </rdfs:comment>
    </owl:ObjectProperty>

    <!-- EMBODIMENT BRIDGE COMPONENTS -->
    <owl:Class rdf:about="#EmbodimentClaim">
        <rdfs:label>Embodiment Claim</rdfs:label>
        <rdfs:comment>A structured claim: A with B embodies C wrt D. All four components required.</rdfs:comment>

        <!-- RESTRICTION: Must have intuition (A) -->
        <rdfs:subClassOf>
            <owl:Restriction>
                <owl:onProperty rdf:resource="#intuition"/>
                <owl:minCardinality rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#nonNegativeInteger">1</owl:minCardinality>
            </owl:Restriction>
        </rdfs:subClassOf>

        <!-- RESTRICTION: Must have compareFrom (B) -->
        <rdfs:subClassOf>
            <owl:Restriction>
                <owl:onProperty rdf:resource="#compareFrom"/>
                <owl:minCardinality rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#nonNegativeInteger">1</owl:minCardinality>
            </owl:Restriction>
        </rdfs:subClassOf>

        <!-- RESTRICTION: Must have mapsTo (C) -->
        <rdfs:subClassOf>
            <owl:Restriction>
                <owl:onProperty rdf:resource="#mapsTo"/>
                <owl:minCardinality rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#nonNegativeInteger">1</owl:minCardinality>
            </owl:Restriction>
        </rdfs:subClassOf>

        <!-- RESTRICTION: Must have analogicalPattern (D) - the actual pattern -->
        <rdfs:subClassOf>
            <owl:Restriction>
                <owl:onProperty rdf:resource="#analogicalPattern"/>
                <owl:minCardinality rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#nonNegativeInteger">1</owl:minCardinality>
            </owl:Restriction>
        </rdfs:subClassOf>
    </owl:Class>

    <owl:ObjectProperty rdf:about="#intuition">
        <rdfs:label>intuition (A)</rdfs:label>
        <rdfs:comment>The thing you're thinking about (A in the bridge)</rdfs:comment>
        <rdfs:domain rdf:resource="#EmbodimentClaim"/>
    </owl:ObjectProperty>

    <owl:ObjectProperty rdf:about="#compareFrom">
        <rdfs:label>compare_from (B)</rdfs:label>
        <rdfs:comment>What you're comparing your intuition from (B in the bridge)</rdfs:comment>
        <rdfs:domain rdf:resource="#EmbodimentClaim"/>
    </owl:ObjectProperty>

    <owl:ObjectProperty rdf:about="#mapsTo">
        <rdfs:label>maps_to (C)</rdfs:label>
        <rdfs:comment>Where the pattern maps to (C in the bridge)</rdfs:comment>
        <rdfs:domain rdf:resource="#EmbodimentClaim"/>
    </owl:ObjectProperty>

    <owl:ObjectProperty rdf:about="#analogicalPattern">
        <rdfs:label>analogical_pattern (D)</rdfs:label>
        <rdfs:comment>THE ACTUAL PATTERN being discovered via analogy (D in the bridge). This is what the claim is really about - the analogical relationship.</rdfs:comment>
        <rdfs:domain rdf:resource="#EmbodimentClaim"/>
    </owl:ObjectProperty>

    <!-- MANIFESTS: Building a PATTERN LATTICE -->
    <owl:ObjectProperty rdf:about="#manifests">
        <rdfs:label>manifests</rdfs:label>
        <rdfs:comment>
BUILDING A PATTERN LATTICE: Multi-dimensional, not one-shot.
Trace the pattern UP to abstract form AND DOWN to specific instances.
Result is a LATTICE, not a single match.
Pragmatic convergence: stop when "it no longer matters" (Zeno resolution).
        </rdfs:comment>
    </owl:ObjectProperty>

    <!-- PATTERN LATTICE STRUCTURE -->
    <owl:Class rdf:about="#PatternLattice">
        <rdfs:label>Pattern Lattice</rdfs:label>
        <rdfs:comment>The multi-dimensional structure built during manifests. Abstract patterns subsume specific ones.</rdfs:comment>
        <rdfs:subClassOf>
            <owl:Restriction>
                <owl:onProperty rdf:resource="#abstractionLevel"/>
                <owl:minCardinality rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#nonNegativeInteger">1</owl:minCardinality>
            </owl:Restriction>
        </rdfs:subClassOf>
    </owl:Class>

    <owl:Class rdf:about="#ValidatedLattice">
        <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="#PatternLattice"/>
        <rdfs:label>Validated Lattice</rdfs:label>
        <rdfs:comment>A PatternLattice that has been validated as instantiating pattern_of_is_a. Can be promoted to Reality.</rdfs:comment>
        <rdfs:subClassOf>
            <owl:Restriction>
                <owl:onProperty rdf:resource="#instantiates"/>
                <owl:someValuesFrom rdf:resource="#PatternOfIsA"/>
            </owl:Restriction>
        </rdfs:subClassOf>
        <rdfs:subClassOf>
            <owl:Restriction>
                <owl:onProperty rdf:resource="#subsumes"/>
                <owl:minCardinality rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#nonNegativeInteger">1</owl:minCardinality>
            </owl:Restriction>
        </rdfs:subClassOf>
    </owl:Class>

    <owl:Class rdf:about="#GroundedLattice">
        <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="#ValidatedLattice"/>
        <rdfs:label>Grounded Lattice</rdfs:label>
        <rdfs:comment>A ValidatedLattice whose abstract root is grounded in Reality. Ready to program.</rdfs:comment>
        <rdfs:subClassOf>
            <owl:Restriction>
                <owl:onProperty rdf:resource="#partOf"/>
                <owl:someValuesFrom rdf:resource="#Reality"/>
            </owl:Restriction>
        </rdfs:subClassOf>
    </owl:Class>

    <owl:ObjectProperty rdf:about="#subsumes">
        <rdfs:label>subsumes</rdfs:label>
        <rdfs:comment>Abstract pattern subsumes specific pattern in the lattice.</rdfs:comment>
        <rdfs:domain rdf:resource="#PatternLattice"/>
        <rdfs:range rdf:resource="#PatternLattice"/>
        <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#TransitiveProperty"/>
    </owl:ObjectProperty>

    <owl:DatatypeProperty rdf:about="#abstractionLevel">
        <rdfs:label>abstraction_level</rdfs:label>
        <rdfs:comment>How abstract is this pattern? Higher = more general, lower = more specific.</rdfs:comment>
        <rdfs:domain rdf:resource="#PatternLattice"/>
        <rdfs:range rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#integer"/>
    </owl:DatatypeProperty>

    <!-- INSTANTIATES -->
    <owl:ObjectProperty rdf:about="#instantiates">
        <rdfs:label>instantiates</rdfs:label>
        <rdfs:comment>
Standard ontology relation: X is an instance of class Y.
In the UARL chain: "This Manifestation instantiates pattern_of_is_a"
When something instantiates pattern_of_is_a, that instantiation IS what reifies it.
        </rdfs:comment>
    </owl:ObjectProperty>

    <owl:ObjectProperty rdf:about="#hasPartialIsomorphicPattern">
        <rdfs:label>has_partial_isomorphic_pattern</rdfs:label>
        <rdfs:comment>Links a PIOEntity to partial isomorphic pattern fragments it currently carries.</rdfs:comment>
        <rdfs:domain rdf:resource="#PIOEntity"/>
        <rdfs:range rdf:resource="#PartialIsomorphicPattern"/>
    </owl:ObjectProperty>

    <owl:ObjectProperty rdf:about="#hasSelfClaim">
        <rdfs:label>has_self_claim</rdfs:label>
        <rdfs:comment>Links a PIOEntity to explicit claims about what it is.</rdfs:comment>
        <rdfs:domain rdf:resource="#PIOEntity"/>
        <rdfs:range rdf:resource="#ClaimAboutSelf"/>
    </owl:ObjectProperty>

    <owl:DatatypeProperty rdf:about="#patternFragment">
        <rdfs:label>pattern_fragment</rdfs:label>
        <rdfs:domain rdf:resource="#PartialIsomorphicPattern"/>
        <rdfs:range rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#string"/>
    </owl:DatatypeProperty>

    <owl:DatatypeProperty rdf:about="#claimText">
        <rdfs:label>claim_text</rdfs:label>
        <rdfs:domain rdf:resource="#ClaimAboutSelf"/>
        <rdfs:range rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#string"/>
    </owl:DatatypeProperty>

    <!-- PROGRAMS: Entry to Reality -->
    <owl:ObjectProperty rdf:about="#programs">
        <rdfs:label>programs</rdfs:label>
        <rdfs:comment>
ONTOLOGY ENTRY: The proof that this thing CAN exist.
Higher-order instantiates - bridges ontology-addition to Reality.
Only happens after valid instantiation of pattern_of_is_a.
The structure programs into the ontology as is_a(Reality).
        </rdfs:comment>
        <rdfs:domain rdf:resource="#PatternOfIsA"/>
        <rdfs:range rdf:resource="#Reality"/>
    </owl:ObjectProperty>

    <!-- ============================================== -->
    <!-- COMPRESSION + BOUNDEDNESS + SES -->
    <!-- ============================================== -->

    <owl:Class rdf:about="#MinimumSufficientCompression">
        <rdfs:label>Minimum Sufficient Compression (MSC)</rdfs:label>
        <rdfs:comment>Proof artifact that the entity/subgraph is minimally and sufficiently compressed. Strong compression requires MSC + full justifies coverage.</rdfs:comment>
    </owl:Class>

    <owl:Class rdf:about="#DerivationJustification">
        <rdfs:label>Derivation Justification</rdfs:label>
        <rdfs:comment>Typed justification edge in the derivation chain. PatternOfIsA is strongly compressed only when required derivation relations are justified.</rdfs:comment>
    </owl:Class>

    <owl:ObjectProperty rdf:about="#hasMSC">
        <rdfs:label>has_msc</rdfs:label>
        <rdfs:domain rdf:resource="#PatternOfIsA"/>
        <rdfs:range rdf:resource="#MinimumSufficientCompression"/>
    </owl:ObjectProperty>

    <owl:ObjectProperty rdf:about="#justifies">
        <rdfs:label>justifies</rdfs:label>
        <rdfs:domain rdf:resource="#PatternOfIsA"/>
        <rdfs:range rdf:resource="#DerivationJustification"/>
    </owl:ObjectProperty>

    <owl:DatatypeProperty rdf:about="#justifiesEdge">
        <rdfs:label>justifies_edge</rdfs:label>
        <rdfs:domain rdf:resource="#DerivationJustification"/>
        <rdfs:range rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#string"/>
    </owl:DatatypeProperty>

    <owl:DatatypeProperty rdf:about="#catOfCatBounded">
        <rdfs:label>cat_of_cat_bounded</rdfs:label>
        <rdfs:domain rdf:resource="#PatternOfIsA"/>
        <rdfs:range rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#boolean"/>
    </owl:DatatypeProperty>

    <owl:DatatypeProperty rdf:about="#sesTypedDepth">
        <rdfs:label>ses_typed_depth</rdfs:label>
        <rdfs:domain rdf:resource="#PatternOfIsA"/>
        <rdfs:range rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#integer"/>
    </owl:DatatypeProperty>

    <owl:DatatypeProperty rdf:about="#compressionMode">
        <rdfs:label>compression_mode</rdfs:label>
        <rdfs:domain rdf:resource="#PatternOfIsA"/>
        <rdfs:range rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#string"/>
    </owl:DatatypeProperty>

    <!-- ============================================== -->
    <!-- THE PATTERN OF IS_A (self-reifying) -->
    <!-- ============================================== -->

    <owl:Class rdf:about="#PatternOfIsA">
        <rdfs:label>pattern_of_is_a</rdfs:label>
        <rdfs:comment>
The meta-pattern. THE BOOTSTRAP.

is_a, part_of, and instantiates are simultaneously entailed by any one existing.
They all co-arise from the fact that anything exists at all.

pattern_of_is_a traces HOW they bootstrap from symbolicity.

KEY PROPERTY: pattern_of_is_a is SELF-REIFYING.
When something instantiates pattern_of_is_a, that instantiation IS what reifies it.

In this implementation, promotion-grade PatternOfIsA is typed by:
1) hasMSC
2) full justifies coverage
3) catOfCatBounded=true
4) sesTypedDepth maximized threshold
5) programs -> Reality
        </rdfs:comment>
    </owl:Class>

    <owl:Class rdf:about="#StrongCompressionPattern">
        <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="#PatternOfIsA"/>
        <rdfs:label>Strong Compression Pattern</rdfs:label>
        <rdfs:comment>PatternOfIsA satisfying strong compression, bounded chain, and high SES depth.</rdfs:comment>
        <rdfs:subClassOf>
            <owl:Restriction>
                <owl:onProperty rdf:resource="#hasMSC"/>
                <owl:someValuesFrom rdf:resource="#MinimumSufficientCompression"/>
            </owl:Restriction>
        </rdfs:subClassOf>
        <rdfs:subClassOf>
            <owl:Restriction>
                <owl:onProperty rdf:resource="#justifies"/>
                <owl:minCardinality rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#nonNegativeInteger">1</owl:minCardinality>
            </owl:Restriction>
        </rdfs:subClassOf>
        <rdfs:subClassOf>
            <owl:Restriction>
                <owl:onProperty rdf:resource="#catOfCatBounded"/>
                <owl:hasValue rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#boolean">true</owl:hasValue>
            </owl:Restriction>
        </rdfs:subClassOf>
        <rdfs:subClassOf>
            <owl:Restriction>
                <owl:onProperty rdf:resource="#sesTypedDepth"/>
                <owl:someValuesFrom>
                    <rdfs:Datatype>
                        <owl:onDatatype rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#integer"/>
                        <owl:withRestrictions rdf:parseType="Collection">
                            <rdf:Description>
                                <xsd:minInclusive rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#integer">6</xsd:minInclusive>
                            </rdf:Description>
                        </owl:withRestrictions>
                    </rdfs:Datatype>
                </owl:someValuesFrom>
            </owl:Restriction>
        </rdfs:subClassOf>
        <rdfs:subClassOf>
            <owl:Restriction>
                <owl:onProperty rdf:resource="#programs"/>
                <owl:someValuesFrom rdf:resource="#Reality"/>
            </owl:Restriction>
        </rdfs:subClassOf>
    </owl:Class>

    <owl:Class rdf:about="#WeakCompressionPattern">
        <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="#PatternOfIsA"/>
        <rdfs:label>Weak Compression Pattern</rdfs:label>
        <rdfs:comment>PatternOfIsA candidate still missing MSC, justification coverage, boundedness, or SES depth.</rdfs:comment>
    </owl:Class>

    <!-- ============================================== -->
    <!-- AUTOMORPHIC REVELATION CHAINS                  -->
    <!--                                               -->
    <!-- PatternOfIsA is the FIXED POINT where every   -->
    <!-- morphism's own pattern-of-itself is satisfied. -->
    <!-- The definition of is_a IS the bootstrapped    -->
    <!-- co-arising automorphic revelation chains of   -->
    <!-- every other foundational relationship.        -->
    <!--                                               -->
    <!-- The chain for each morphism:                  -->
    <!--   1. primitive_X (raw assertion)              -->
    <!--   2. X embodies containment (part_of)         -->
    <!--   3. containment entails instantiates         -->
    <!--   4. instantiates instantiates (automorphic   -->
    <!--      revelation = pattern_of_X is defined)    -->
    <!--   5. realization of pattern = produces        -->
    <!--   6. production closes to primitive_is_a      -->
    <!--   7. strong = programs, weak = not programs   -->
    <!--   8. both enter ontology as morphism pair     -->
    <!--   9. entire graph = Reality = CatOfCat        -->
    <!--      via automorphism group as chain          -->
    <!--                                               -->
    <!-- GIINT produces chain (bottom-up):             -->
    <!--   Task produces Deliverable                   -->
    <!--   Deliverable produces Component              -->
    <!--   Component produces Feature                  -->
    <!--   Feature produces Project                    -->
    <!--   Project produces Domain (the system)        -->
    <!-- ============================================== -->

    <!-- Pattern-of-X classes: each morphism has its own pattern -->
    <owl:Class rdf:about="#PatternOfPartOf">
        <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="#PatternOfIsA"/>
        <rdfs:label>pattern_of_part_of</rdfs:label>
        <rdfs:comment>The pattern where part_of chains close. An entity's mereological structure is fully justified when every part_of target exists, is typed, and its own part_of chain closes. This pattern is satisfied when the containment hierarchy is complete — every component knows where it lives and what contains it, recursively.</rdfs:comment>
    </owl:Class>

    <owl:Class rdf:about="#PatternOfProduces">
        <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="#PatternOfIsA"/>
        <rdfs:label>pattern_of_produces</rdfs:label>
        <rdfs:comment>The pattern where produces chains close. Bottom-up entailment: having a thing in the ontology means you can reify the thing above it. Deliverable (code+pattern) produces Component (reifiable). Component (all deliverables) produces Feature (reifiable). Feature (all components) produces Project (reifiable). This pattern is satisfied when the generative chain is complete — every level entails the next.</rdfs:comment>
    </owl:Class>

    <owl:Class rdf:about="#PatternOfInstantiates">
        <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="#PatternOfIsA"/>
        <rdfs:label>pattern_of_instantiates</rdfs:label>
        <rdfs:comment>The automorphic revelation pattern. instantiates instantiates = the pattern of how patterns are defined. When instantiation is self-instantiating, you have recognized the automorphism — the pattern that recognizes itself. This is how pattern_of_X is defined for ANY X: X instantiates its own pattern-recognition.</rdfs:comment>
    </owl:Class>

    <!-- GIINT produces restrictions: bottom-up entailment chain -->
    <!-- Each level produces the level above it -->

    <!-- GIINT_Task produces GIINT_Deliverable -->
    <owl:Class rdf:about="#GIINT_Task">
        <rdfs:subClassOf>
            <owl:Restriction>
                <owl:onProperty rdf:resource="#produces"/>
                <owl:someValuesFrom rdf:resource="#GIINT_Deliverable"/>
            </owl:Restriction>
        </rdfs:subClassOf>
    </owl:Class>

    <!-- GIINT_Deliverable produces GIINT_Component -->
    <owl:Class rdf:about="#GIINT_Deliverable">
        <rdfs:subClassOf>
            <owl:Restriction>
                <owl:onProperty rdf:resource="#produces"/>
                <owl:someValuesFrom rdf:resource="#GIINT_Component"/>
            </owl:Restriction>
        </rdfs:subClassOf>
    </owl:Class>

    <!-- GIINT_Component produces GIINT_Feature -->
    <owl:Class rdf:about="#GIINT_Component">
        <rdfs:subClassOf>
            <owl:Restriction>
                <owl:onProperty rdf:resource="#produces"/>
                <owl:someValuesFrom rdf:resource="#GIINT_Feature"/>
            </owl:Restriction>
        </rdfs:subClassOf>
    </owl:Class>

    <!-- GIINT_Feature produces GIINT_Project -->
    <owl:Class rdf:about="#GIINT_Feature">
        <rdfs:subClassOf>
            <owl:Restriction>
                <owl:onProperty rdf:resource="#produces"/>
                <owl:someValuesFrom rdf:resource="#GIINT_Project"/>
            </owl:Restriction>
        </rdfs:subClassOf>
    </owl:Class>

    <!-- ============================================== -->
    <!-- THE BOOTSTRAP: Full co-arising core sentence  -->
    <!--                                               -->
    <!-- ALL SPOs in this sentence are self-arising:    -->
    <!--   is_a, part_of, has_part, instantiates,       -->
    <!--   produces, pattern_of_is_a, primitive_is_a,   -->
    <!--   programs, Reality, embodies, manifests,      -->
    <!--   reifies                                      -->
    <!--                                               -->
    <!-- The core sentence:                            -->
    <!--   from Reality and is(Reality):                -->
    <!--   primitive_is_a IS a type of is_a             -->
    <!--   is_a embodies part_of                        -->
    <!--   (part_of entailed by is_a, itself as a       -->
    <!--    triple, entails produces — the NEED for     -->
    <!--    the new label IS instantiation)              -->
    <!--   part_of manifests produces                   -->
    <!--   produces reifies produces is_a               -->
    <!--     pattern_of_is_a                            -->
    <!--   pattern_of_is_a programs Reality             -->
    <!--                                               -->
    <!-- This sequence, though open-ended in            -->
    <!-- composition, has the alphabet that describes   -->
    <!-- anything in a bootstrapped way. We call that   -->
    <!-- PROGRAMS. The math: this stops when            -->
    <!-- constraints are inferential in the logic =     -->
    <!-- endofunctor D:[D→D], domain as fixed point     -->
    <!-- autology ABOUT is_a.                          -->
    <!--                                               -->
    <!-- Aut: we know how to explain what is and isn't  -->
    <!-- it = bijective map about domain constraints.   -->
    <!-- Each predicate requires bijective inclusion    -->
    <!-- map: from domain of property what it requires  -->
    <!-- + entity having it must be inside constraining -->
    <!-- domain.                                       -->
    <!-- ============================================== -->

    <!-- PROPERTY CHAIN AXIOMS: entailments OWL doesn't know natively -->
    <!-- These encode the core sentence as OWL2 property chains -->

    <!-- is_a entails part_of: if X is_a Y then X must be part_of something -->
    <!-- OWL2: SubObjectPropertyOf(ObjectPropertyChain(isA) partOf) -->
    <!-- This means: anything with an is_a MUST also have a part_of -->
    <!-- Pellet enforces this via property chain reasoning -->
    <rdf:Description>
        <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Axiom"/>
        <rdfs:comment>Core sentence step: is_a embodies part_of. Claiming X is_a Y entails X is SOMEWHERE. is_a cannot exist without containment.</rdfs:comment>
    </rdf:Description>

    <!-- ============================================== -->
    <!-- CORE SENTENCE PROPERTY CHAIN AXIOMS            -->
    <!-- Each axiom encodes one re-derivation step.     -->
    <!-- Pellet's transitive closure over these IS the  -->
    <!-- proof mechanism for self-similarity.            -->
    <!--                                                 -->
    <!-- For every SPO triple: "is this relationship     -->
    <!-- defined in a way that abstractly re-derives     -->
    <!-- this relationship?" If yes for ALL triples =    -->
    <!-- strong compression = ONT. Partial = SOUP.       -->
    <!-- ============================================== -->

    <!-- J3: is_a embodies part_of — claiming X is_a Y entails X is SOMEWHERE -->
    <!-- Chain: isA → embodies → partOf (is_a entails containment) -->
    <owl:ObjectProperty rdf:about="#partOf">
        <owl:propertyChainAxiom rdf:parseType="Collection">
            <rdf:Description rdf:about="#isA"/>
            <rdf:Description rdf:about="#embodies"/>
        </owl:propertyChainAxiom>
    </owl:ObjectProperty>

    <!-- J3 inverse: part_of + is_a → is_a (transitivity through containment) -->
    <!-- If X part_of Y and Y is_a Z, then X is_a Z -->
    <owl:ObjectProperty rdf:about="#isA">
        <owl:propertyChainAxiom rdf:parseType="Collection">
            <rdf:Description rdf:about="#partOf"/>
            <rdf:Description rdf:about="#isA"/>
        </owl:propertyChainAxiom>
    </owl:ObjectProperty>

    <!-- J4: partOf entails instantiates — containment entails instantiation -->
    <!-- Chain: partOf → isA → instantiates (being part of something typed = you ARE an instance) -->
    <!-- If X partOf Y and Y isA Z, then X instantiates the pattern of Z -->
    <owl:ObjectProperty rdf:about="#instantiates">
        <owl:propertyChainAxiom rdf:parseType="Collection">
            <rdf:Description rdf:about="#partOf"/>
            <rdf:Description rdf:about="#isA"/>
        </owl:propertyChainAxiom>
    </owl:ObjectProperty>

    <!-- J5: instantiates + instantiates → embodies (automorphic revelation) -->
    <!-- When instantiation is self-instantiating, you have recognized the -->
    <!-- automorphism — the pattern that recognizes itself. This IS how -->
    <!-- pattern_of_X is defined for ANY X. The self-application of -->
    <!-- instantiates IS the embodies relationship (it bears its own pattern). -->
    <owl:ObjectProperty rdf:about="#embodies">
        <owl:propertyChainAxiom rdf:parseType="Collection">
            <rdf:Description rdf:about="#instantiates"/>
            <rdf:Description rdf:about="#instantiates"/>
        </owl:propertyChainAxiom>
    </owl:ObjectProperty>

    <!-- J6: part_of manifests produces — containment manifests generativity -->
    <!-- Chain: partOf → manifests → produces (if X part_of Y, Y produces X-like things) -->
    <owl:ObjectProperty rdf:about="#produces">
        <owl:propertyChainAxiom rdf:parseType="Collection">
            <rdf:Description rdf:about="#partOf"/>
            <rdf:Description rdf:about="#manifests"/>
        </owl:propertyChainAxiom>
    </owl:ObjectProperty>

    <!-- J7: produces reifies PatternOfIsA — the alphabet recognition step -->
    <!-- Chain: produces → reifies (what you produce enters SOUP as PIOEntity) -->
    <owl:ObjectProperty rdf:about="#reifies">
        <owl:propertyChainAxiom rdf:parseType="Collection">
            <rdf:Description rdf:about="#produces"/>
            <rdf:Description rdf:about="#embodies"/>
        </owl:propertyChainAxiom>
    </owl:ObjectProperty>

    <!-- J8: PatternOfIsA produces programs — atomic description = programs -->
    <!-- Chain: reifies + produces → programs (reified pattern that produces = programs) -->
    <owl:ObjectProperty rdf:about="#programs">
        <owl:propertyChainAxiom rdf:parseType="Collection">
            <rdf:Description rdf:about="#reifies"/>
            <rdf:Description rdf:about="#produces"/>
        </owl:propertyChainAxiom>
    </owl:ObjectProperty>

    <!-- J9: programs → partOf Reality (circle closes) -->
    <!-- Chain: programs + isA → partOf (what programs Reality is part of Reality) -->
    <owl:ObjectProperty rdf:about="#partOf">
        <owl:propertyChainAxiom rdf:parseType="Collection">
            <rdf:Description rdf:about="#programs"/>
            <rdf:Description rdf:about="#isA"/>
        </owl:propertyChainAxiom>
    </owl:ObjectProperty>

    <!-- Justification edges: full co-arising core sentence -->

    <owl:NamedIndividual rdf:about="#Bootstrap_J1_Reality_IsA_Reality">
        <rdf:type rdf:resource="#DerivationJustification"/>
        <rdf:type rdf:resource="#Entity"/>
        <justifiesEdge xmlns="http://sanctuary.ai/uarl#">Reality:isA:Reality</justifiesEdge>
        <rdfs:comment>from Reality and is(Reality): is_a exists because Reality exists. Self-referential ground. Reality is_a Reality is the fixed point that everything traces back to.</rdfs:comment>
        <isA xmlns="http://sanctuary.ai/uarl#" rdf:resource="#Reality"/>
        <partOf xmlns="http://sanctuary.ai/uarl#" rdf:resource="#THE_PatternOfIsA"/>
        <produces xmlns="http://sanctuary.ai/uarl#" rdf:resource="#Bootstrap_J2_PrimitiveIsA_IsA_IsA"/>
    </owl:NamedIndividual>

    <owl:NamedIndividual rdf:about="#Bootstrap_J2_PrimitiveIsA_IsA_IsA">
        <rdf:type rdf:resource="#DerivationJustification"/>
        <rdf:type rdf:resource="#Entity"/>
        <justifiesEdge xmlns="http://sanctuary.ai/uarl#">primitive_is_a:isA:isA</justifiesEdge>
        <rdfs:comment>primitive_is_a IS a type of is_a. Any claim X is_a Y is first a primitive_is_a — an unvalidated assertion entering SOUP. primitive_is_a is itself self-arising as a kind of is_a.</rdfs:comment>
        <isA xmlns="http://sanctuary.ai/uarl#" rdf:resource="#Reality"/>
        <partOf xmlns="http://sanctuary.ai/uarl#" rdf:resource="#THE_PatternOfIsA"/>
        <produces xmlns="http://sanctuary.ai/uarl#" rdf:resource="#Bootstrap_J3_IsA_Embodies_PartOf"/>
    </owl:NamedIndividual>

    <owl:NamedIndividual rdf:about="#Bootstrap_J3_IsA_Embodies_PartOf">
        <rdf:type rdf:resource="#DerivationJustification"/>
        <rdf:type rdf:resource="#Entity"/>
        <justifiesEdge xmlns="http://sanctuary.ai/uarl#">isA:embodies:partOf</justifiesEdge>
        <rdfs:comment>is_a embodies part_of. If X is_a Y, then X MUST BE SOMEWHERE — it has containment. part_of co-arises with is_a because you cannot claim something IS something without it BEING somewhere. The entailment is: is_a → part_of.</rdfs:comment>
        <isA xmlns="http://sanctuary.ai/uarl#" rdf:resource="#Reality"/>
        <partOf xmlns="http://sanctuary.ai/uarl#" rdf:resource="#THE_PatternOfIsA"/>
        <produces xmlns="http://sanctuary.ai/uarl#" rdf:resource="#Bootstrap_J4_PartOf_Entails_Instantiates"/>
    </owl:NamedIndividual>

    <owl:NamedIndividual rdf:about="#Bootstrap_J4_PartOf_Entails_Instantiates">
        <rdf:type rdf:resource="#DerivationJustification"/>
        <rdf:type rdf:resource="#Entity"/>
        <justifiesEdge xmlns="http://sanctuary.ai/uarl#">partOf:entails:instantiates</justifiesEdge>
        <rdfs:comment>part_of entailed by is_a, ITSELF AS A TRIPLE, entails instantiates. The fact that "X is_a Y" creates "X part_of Z" means we have a TRIPLE (X, part_of, Z). This triple's existence IS instantiation — we needed a new label ("produces") and the need for it is itself an instantiation event. instantiates co-arises here.</rdfs:comment>
        <isA xmlns="http://sanctuary.ai/uarl#" rdf:resource="#Reality"/>
        <partOf xmlns="http://sanctuary.ai/uarl#" rdf:resource="#THE_PatternOfIsA"/>
        <produces xmlns="http://sanctuary.ai/uarl#" rdf:resource="#Bootstrap_J5_Instantiates_Necessitates_Produces"/>
    </owl:NamedIndividual>

    <owl:NamedIndividual rdf:about="#Bootstrap_J5_Instantiates_Necessitates_Produces">
        <rdf:type rdf:resource="#DerivationJustification"/>
        <rdf:type rdf:resource="#Entity"/>
        <justifiesEdge xmlns="http://sanctuary.ai/uarl#">instantiates:necessitates:produces</justifiesEdge>
        <rdfs:comment>instantiates necessitates we use a new label we call produces. The instantiation event (creating the part_of triple) REQUIRES us to name what the container DOES — it produces things of that type. produces is the label for this generativity. produces co-arises from instantiates.</rdfs:comment>
        <isA xmlns="http://sanctuary.ai/uarl#" rdf:resource="#Reality"/>
        <partOf xmlns="http://sanctuary.ai/uarl#" rdf:resource="#THE_PatternOfIsA"/>
        <produces xmlns="http://sanctuary.ai/uarl#" rdf:resource="#Bootstrap_J6_PartOf_Manifests_Produces"/>
    </owl:NamedIndividual>

    <owl:NamedIndividual rdf:about="#Bootstrap_J6_PartOf_Manifests_Produces">
        <rdf:type rdf:resource="#DerivationJustification"/>
        <rdf:type rdf:resource="#Entity"/>
        <justifiesEdge xmlns="http://sanctuary.ai/uarl#">partOf:manifests:produces</justifiesEdge>
        <rdfs:comment>part_of manifests produces. Containment manifests generativity. If X is part_of Y, then Y produces X-like things. This is the EMR manifests step — the structure becomes visible.</rdfs:comment>
        <isA xmlns="http://sanctuary.ai/uarl#" rdf:resource="#Reality"/>
        <partOf xmlns="http://sanctuary.ai/uarl#" rdf:resource="#THE_PatternOfIsA"/>
        <produces xmlns="http://sanctuary.ai/uarl#" rdf:resource="#Bootstrap_J7_Produces_Reifies_PatternOfIsA"/>
    </owl:NamedIndividual>

    <owl:NamedIndividual rdf:about="#Bootstrap_J7_Produces_Reifies_PatternOfIsA">
        <rdf:type rdf:resource="#DerivationJustification"/>
        <rdf:type rdf:resource="#Entity"/>
        <justifiesEdge xmlns="http://sanctuary.ai/uarl#">produces:reifies:PatternOfIsA</justifiesEdge>
        <rdfs:comment>produces reifies as pattern_of_is_a. The sequence is_a→part_of→instantiates→produces, even though open-ended in composition, has an ALPHABET that should describe anything in a bootstrapped way. Recognizing this alphabet IS pattern_of_is_a. pattern_of_is_a is self-arising — it IS the recognition that the bootstrap has a pattern.</rdfs:comment>
        <isA xmlns="http://sanctuary.ai/uarl#" rdf:resource="#Reality"/>
        <partOf xmlns="http://sanctuary.ai/uarl#" rdf:resource="#THE_PatternOfIsA"/>
        <produces xmlns="http://sanctuary.ai/uarl#" rdf:resource="#Bootstrap_J8_PatternOfIsA_Produces_Programs"/>
    </owl:NamedIndividual>

    <owl:NamedIndividual rdf:about="#Bootstrap_J8_PatternOfIsA_Produces_Programs">
        <rdf:type rdf:resource="#DerivationJustification"/>
